<item>
            <title>[SOLR-11322] Omit min/max aggregations when there are no values in a bucket</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-11322</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;min/max currently return NaN when there are no values for a bucket.&lt;br/&gt;
This is problematic in JSON format, which has no support for NaN.  It becomes a bigger issue for typed support like long values where NaN doesn&apos;t make sense, and even worse for String fields, since &apos;NaN&apos; is an actual valid string value.  Instead, we should just omit the aggregation value altogether.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
